JavaScript Only Code (index.js)

// Define the add function in JavaScript
function add(x, y) {
    return x + y;
}

// Call the function and log the result
document.write("Result of 5 + 7:", add(5, 7)); // Output: 12

HTML File (index.html)

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>JavaScript Example</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>JavaScript Example</h1>
    <script src="index.js"></script>
</body>
</html>

How to Run
1. Save index.js and index.html in the same directory.
2. Open index.html in a web browser.
3. Open the browser console (F12 > Console) to see the output:
